@startuml
left to right direction
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam roundcorner 12
skinparam defaultTextAlignment center
skinparam rectangle {
  BackgroundColor #F8FAFC
  BorderColor #475569
}
skinparam database {
  BackgroundColor #FEF3C7
  BorderColor #B45309
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FFF7ED
  BorderColor #C2410C
}

title EduSecure Current-State Data Flow Diagram - Level 1

rectangle "Client Boundary" {
  rectangle "Student\n<<External Entity>>" as Student #E0F2FE
  rectangle "Lecturer / Admin\n<<External Entity>>" as Staff #E0F2FE
  rectangle "Authenticator App\n<<External Entity>>" as Authenticator #E0F2FE
  database "D0 Browser sessionStorage\npending MFA challenge only\n(no JWT)" as D0
}

rectangle "EduSecure Application Boundary" {
  rectangle "P1 Auth and Session Handling\nAuthController + AuthService" as P1 #DBEAFE
  rectangle "P2 MFA Challenge Handling\nMfaService" as P2 #DBEAFE
  rectangle "P3 Submission Protection and Retrieval\nSubmissionService" as P3 #DBEAFE
  rectangle "P4 Grade Integrity Handling\nGradeService" as P4 #DBEAFE
  rectangle "P5 Audit Integrity Recording\nAuditService" as P5 #DBEAFE
}

rectangle "Persistence Boundary" {
  database "D1 PostgreSQL\nusers, roles, MFA metadata,\nsubmission metadata, grades, audit logs" as D1
  database "D2 Submission Ciphertext Store\nciphertext blobs by storedFileReference" as D2
}

Student --> P1 : registration/login\n/api/auth/* requests
Staff --> P1 : login/logout\n/api/auth/* requests
P1 --> Student : Set-Cookie auth session\ncurrent-user response
P1 --> Staff : Set-Cookie auth session\ncurrent-user response
P1 --> D1 : read/write users, roles,\npassword hashes, session claims input
P1 --> P2 : start MFA challenge when required
P1 --> D0 : store MFA pending challenge metadata

Student --> P2 : MFA setup / verify / disable requests
Staff --> P2 : MFA setup / verify / disable requests
P2 --> Authenticator : otpauth URI / manual key
Authenticator --> P2 : TOTP code
P2 --> D1 : encrypted MFA secret, challenge records,\nrecovery-code hashes
P2 --> P1 : authenticated MFA result for cookie issuance
P2 --> D0 : clear pending challenge after success/failure path

Student --> P3 : submission create / metadata / content requests
Staff --> P3 : submission review / content access requests
P3 --> D1 : assignment lookup, submission metadata,\ndigest, signature, verification state, wrapped key metadata
P3 --> D2 : store ciphertext / read ciphertext
P3 --> Student : metadata-only response\nor plaintext on explicit content retrieval
P3 --> Staff : metadata-only response\nor plaintext on authorised content retrieval
P3 --> P5 : SUBMISSION_CREATED\nSUBMISSION_VERIFIED / FAILED\nSUBMISSION_CONTENT_ACCESSED

Staff --> P4 : create/update/retrieve grade requests
Student --> P4 : own-grade retrieval request
P4 --> D1 : read verified submission state\nwrite/read grade records
P4 --> Staff : grade create/update/review responses
P4 --> Student : own-grade response only
P4 --> P5 : GRADE_CREATED / GRADE_UPDATED

P5 --> D1 : append audit log row with\nHMAC-SHA-256 integrity chain

note right of P3
Plaintext enters the backend once for submission handling.
The backend computes the SHA-256 digest,
creates/verifies signature metadata,
then encrypts content at rest with AES-GCM.
end note

note right of D2
Ciphertext is stored separately from PostgreSQL metadata.
Normal metadata responses do not expose
storedFileReference, nonce values,
or wrapped content-encryption keys.
end note
@enduml


